Quote: Flax, Native, n. The European flax is <i>Linum usitatissimum</i>, N.O. <i>Linea</i>.  There is a species in Australia, <i>Linum marginale</i>, Cunn., N.O. <i>Linacea</i>, called Native Flax, In New Zealand, the Phormium  is called <i>Native Flax</i>. See next word [<i>Flax, New Zealand</i>].
